================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

RWKV-LM (RWKV reference architecture)
  Upstream: https://github.com/BlinkDL/RWKV-LM
  Used in:  our Rust inference runtime at krunch-rust/src/rwkv.rs is a
            re-implementation of the RWKV-v4 forward pass from the
            published RWKV-v4 paper and reference implementation.
            MSL kernels in krunch-rust/src/backend/mtl.rs and the fused
            WKV kernel at scripts/metal_wkv/wkv.metal are clean-room
            ports of the reference CUDA implementation.
  License:  Apache-2.0.

Krunch (AAAI 2025 paper reference implementation)
  Upstream: https://github.com/jkooy/Krunch
  Used in:  vendor/Krunch/ (reference Python implementation, not shipped
            in service binaries). The initial Rust inference runtime
            was derived from this reference. Training pipeline
            scripts (scripts/train_krunch_phase11.py, related tooling)
            follow the Krunch training recipe.
  License:  Research use under Apache-2.0, consistent with the RWKV
            dependency.

SentencePiece (optional runtime dependency)
  Upstream: https://github.com/google/sentencepiece
  Used in:  dynamically linked via the `sentencepiece` Rust crate for
            tokenization. Not statically bundled in default service
            binaries.
  License:  Apache-2.0.

Rust crate dependencies
  All direct and transitive Rust crate dependencies are permissive
